snippet.textDisplay:
Last month i visited sukker, jacobabad, shikarpur bcuz of family functions it was the first time I saw that I belong to this grand family. there was so many people I Saw first time in my life my czn said they are clos relatives.
I was literally stunned by the unfathomable hospitality and compassion that sindhi people have shown to me as a karachiite I was blown away by their true spirit and love.
And not just our relatives even though the friends of my czn paid so much gratitude and respect to us that it was hard to believe that they weren't my friends.
I even started to understand sindhi language and now I can understand almost completely.
unfortunately I can't speak sindhi but I'll try to learn it from someone very close to me.
And BTW i got to learn this sentence from my czn's friends.
پیسہ نا وٹی۔
It means don't take the money from him.
Bcuz when I was there they didn't let me pay for anything.
Even when I sneak out and try to pay without letting them know they just shout from far away "don't take the money" and that's it.😅
It was a remarkable experience sindhi people are compassionate beautiful and wonderfully hospitable❤.
